# Spatialâ€“Temporal Hypergraph Enhanced Meta-Learning for Eye Movement Classification

This repository contains the implementation of a **few-shot, semi-supervised eye movement classification framework** using **spatialâ€“temporal hypergraph learning combined with meta-learning**.  
The model is designed to achieve **robust cross-subject generalization** under limited labeled data conditions.

---

## ğŸ” Overview

Eye movement recognition using EMG/EOG signals is critical for:
- Humanâ€“Computer Interaction (HCI)
- Assistive technologies
- Neurophysiological assessment

Traditional deep learning approaches require large labeled datasets and fail under inter-subject variability.  
To overcome this, we propose a **CNN + Hypergraph + Meta-Learning** framework with **pseudo-labeling**.

---

## âœ¨ Key Contributions

- âœ… Spatialâ€“temporal **hypergraph modeling** to capture higher-order dependencies
- âœ… **Few-shot meta-learning** for rapid subject adaptation
- âœ… **Semi-supervised pseudo-labeling** to reduce annotation dependency
- âœ… Structural regularization using **hypergraph consistency losses**
- âœ… Evaluated under **Leave-One-Subject-Out (LOSO)** protocol

---

## ğŸ§© Graph vs Hypergraph Representation

<img src="figures/graph_vs_hypergraph.png" width="700"/>

**Why Hypergraph?**  
Unlike conventional graphs (pairwise edges), hypergraphs allow **one hyperedge to connect multiple nodes**, enabling modeling of group-wise temporal dependencies in EMG/EOG signals.

---

## ğŸ—ï¸ Proposed Architecture

<img src="figures/architecture.png" width="800"/>

### Pipeline:
1. CNN-based temporal feature extraction
2. Spatialâ€“temporal hypergraph construction
3. Hyperedge message passing
4. Meta-learning (Support & Query sets)
5. Pseudo-labeling for unlabeled samples

---

## ğŸ§ª Dataset & Classes

- **Signal Type:** Two-channel EMG/EOG
- **Evaluation:** LOSO cross-validation
- **Classes (6):**
  - CN â€“ Center
  - MD â€“ Move Down
  - ML â€“ Move Left
  - MP â€“ Move Right
  - MR â€“ Move Right
  - MU â€“ Move Up

